	   <tr><td colspan=2>There is only ONE reason for this item.<br><br>In the Plane of Hate, for a while, there was a robe dropping, mostly on the second floor, called the Neriak Ceremonial Robe <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=5193" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=5193</a> ...<br><br>This robe was put in by VI to just give the 'look' that VI wanted the mob to have.<br><br>Same thing with this sword here... only what the sword does is breaks VI's own damage limits. This sword is a way for the mob to put out the damage they want it to. Hence the above reference to the robe for the 'look', the sword is for the 'damage'. <br><br>This sword will never be equipable, nor will it ever even be considered to be. VI's log arythem's for BASE damage are capped, by thier own means. This sword is a way for them to avoid thier own cap through thier own way. <br><br>And they had the nerve to say wizard's 'Manaburn is working as intended', THEN nerf it when they are makeing thier own mobs nearly unstoppable. Yhea, thats balance.<br><br>/rude VI for the tease<br>&nbsp;<br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=357723 target=_new>Orocular</a><br><a href=HTTP://www.keepersofoak.org target=_new>Keepers of Oak</a><br><a href=HTTP://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency target=_new>The Rathe</a><br><br></td></tr>
